[{"id":"VR005052","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<div>\n<div class=\"stimulus_reference\">\n<div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure presents a diagram of an electron source to the left of a vertical barrier with a single slit. To the right of the barrier is a rectangular plate and further to the right a smaller rectangular detector.  \" height=\"169\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/537/VR005052.g02.png\" width=\"455\" /></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n<p class=\"stem_paragraph\">A beam of electrons with the same de Broglie wavelength is directed through a narrow slit whose width is about the same size as the electrons’ wavelength. Electrons travel toward a detector that measures electron speed. The detector initially measures the speed of the electrons as <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"v sub 0\"><math alttext=\"v sub 0\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><msub><mrow><mi>v</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>0</mn></mrow></msub></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span>. A thick lead plate is then placed halfway between the source and detector, as shown, that absorbs all the electrons that hit it. Which of the following predictions is correct about how the new electron speed <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"v sub 1\"><math alttext=\"v sub 1\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><msub><mrow><mi>v</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow></msub></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> measured by the detector compares with <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"v sub 0\"><math alttext=\"v sub 0\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><msub><mrow><mi>v</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>0</mn></mrow></msub></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span>?</p>\n","rubricRef":"VR005052_rubric","choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"v sub 1 is less than v sub 0\"><math alttext=\"v sub 1 is less than v sub 0\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><msub><mrow><mi>v</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow></msub><mo>&lt;</mo><msub><mrow><mi>v</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>0</mn></mrow></msub></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span>. Some electrons diffracted by the slit will also be diffracted by the plate, and they will lose energy due to their interaction with the plate.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"v sub 1 is greater than v sub 0\"><math alttext=\"v sub 1 is greater than v sub 0\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><msub><mrow><mi>v</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow></msub><mo>&gt;</mo><msub><mrow><mi>v</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>0</mn></mrow></msub></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span>. Some electrons diffracted by the slit will also be diffracted by the plate, and only the fastest electrons will arrive at the detector.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"v sub 1 is equal to v sub 0\"><math alttext=\"v sub 1 is equal to v sub 0\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><msub><mrow><mi>v</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow></msub><mo>=</mo><msub><mrow><mi>v</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>0</mn></mrow></msub></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span>. Some electrons diffracted by the slit will also diffract around the plate, without affecting the electron speed.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"v sub 1 is equal to 0\"><math alttext=\"v sub 1 is equal to 0\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><msub><mrow><mi>v</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span>, because the plate will prevent all the electrons from reaching the detector.</p>"],"answer":2}]